      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GARY INDIANA (1) was prominent throughout when winning two back then got further back last time but came home hard into second and beaten 4.5 lengths at this track (23.20). Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. One of the contenders. STOCK'S GIFT (8) turned in a fair 4th placed finish last time at this track over 400m (23.38). Form here at the trip sound including four wins. Leading chance. CHUTZPAH (7) is a good beginner but will need a quick break. Latest effort finished 4th in a Grade 5 on May 16 over 400m at this track behind Pitman Go Quick beaten 6 lengths (23.31). Looks suited here and can measure up. EVEN ME (2) can fill a top-three spot.",
